"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007185","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-11-21","<p>Officials from the Oil and Gas Authority (OGA) have visited the Preston New Road site since the red traffic light events. The OGA is closely monitoring operations at the site and is continuing to scrutinise data from the seismic monitoring array.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-11-21T17:18:04.803Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007185/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007185/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007185/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-11-14","Fracking: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the Oil and Gas Authority has visited the Preston New Road shale gas site since the four seismic events of greater than the red light 0.5ML threshold that occurred between 26 October 2018 and 4 November 2018.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","191381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007186","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-11-21","<p>Yes.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-11-21T10:35:59.83Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007186/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007186/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007186/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-11-14","Fracking: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether the Environment Agency has visited the Preston New Road shale gas site since the four seismic events of greater than the red light 0.5ML threshold that occurred between 26 October 2018 and 4 November 2018.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","191382"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007188","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-11-19","<p>The Department constantly monitors the UK’s gas security of supply. The Department and Ofgem conduct an annual statutory security of supply report that was most recently submitted to Parliament on 6<sup>th</sup> November 2018 (Can be found <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/753170/BEIS_Ofgem_Statutory_Security_of_Supply_Report_2018.pdf" target="_blank">here</a>). In addition, in October 2015, the then Secretary of State for Energy &amp; Climate Change committed to a 5-year cycle of reviews of the UK’s gas security of supply. The most recent publication in this series was in October 2017 (Can be found <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/651297/gas-security-supply-assessment.pdf" target="_blank">here</a>).</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-11-19T15:41:45.37Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007188/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007188/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007188/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-11-14","Natural Gas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to answers provided to questions 106 and 117 at the Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy Committee Oral evidence session on gas storage on 31 October 2018, HC 1666, whether his Department is conducting a review of the UK's gas security.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","191485"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007480","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-28","<p>The Department is committed to ensuring that the National Health Service fully embeds the Prevent Statutory Duty of 2015 within its safeguarding responsibilities.</p><p>Great strides have been taken to embed Prevent within the health sector to date. For example, since the Prevent Duty made training mandatory over 830,000 NHS staff have received Basic Prevent Awareness training and over 470,000 have attended advanced training.</p><p>The Department is committed to engaging with relevant professional bodies and ensure that further opportunities to develop bespoke training for health professionals are undertaken.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2018-11-28T14:50:55.367Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007480/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007480/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007480/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-11-14","NHS: Counter-terrorism","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what plans they have to implement the Prevent Strategy within the NHS as a safeguarding measure to protect those with care and support needs.","false","Biography information for Baroness Afshar",,"Baroness Afshar","HL11484"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007482","Treasury","false","2018-11-28","<p>The Government has today laid before Parliament a Written Ministerial Statement entitled “Exiting the European Union – publications” and published cross-Whitehall analysis of the economic and fiscal effects of leaving the EU. The fiscal impacts are available on p. 71-76 of this document, “EU Exit: Long-term economic analysis, November 2018”, which is available on Gov.uk and from the Printed Paper Office.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2018-11-28T17:13:17.837Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007482/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007482/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007482/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-11-14","Brexit: Costs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what estimate they have made of what the cost to the UK Government of leaving the European Union will be in each year until 2039.","false","Biography information for Lord Bassam of Brighton",,"Lord Bassam of Brighton","HL11485"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007483","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-28","<p>As the Prime Minister has said, the UK has secured a deal which is in our national interest, and will ensure our smooth and orderly departure from the EU. The Prime Minister has also made clear that our future relationship with the EU should be broader in scope than with any other third country, and that it should allow us to maintain our close diplomatic, economic and political relations. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office will play a key role through its network of Posts which are Her Majesty’s Government’s primary tool to influence and engage EU Member States.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2018-11-28T16:29:01.373Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007483/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007483/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007483/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-11-14","UK Relations with EU","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what arrangements they intend to put in place to maintain diplomatic, economic and political relations with the European Union after Brexit; and to what extent any such arrangements will be a continuation of those already in place.","false","Biography information for Lord Bassam of Brighton",,"Lord Bassam of Brighton","HL11486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007484","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-11-28","<p>The information is not centrally held and could be obtained only at disproportionate cost. However, all pregnant women in custody have an individual care and management plan that is communicated to all staff and all pregnant women are seen by a mid-wife at least fortnightly or as required.</p><p>Healthcare in prisons is provided by trained medics and nurses, but we have also made training on dealing with pregnant women available to all prison officers.</p><p>We know it is extremely rare for a woman to give birth in prison - because every step is taken to get them to hospital - but those unique cases are invariably down to the unpredictability of labour.</p>",,"Lord Keen of Elie",,"2018-11-28T13:55:32.41Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007484/answer","Biography information for Lord Keen of Elie","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007484/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007484/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-11-14","Prisoners: Childbirth","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many female prisoners gave birth in custody in each of the last five years; and, of those, how many did so in cells.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL11487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007485","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-28","<p>Network Rail are progressing the design and development of the Western Rail Link to Heathrow and recently concluded a statutory consultation on the proposed alignment of the route. This is a major step for the scheme and is required before Network Rail can submit its planned application to the Planning Inspectorate for the necessary consents in 2019.</p><p> </p><p>In respect of the proposed Southern Access scheme, the Department undertook market testing earlier this year. This is the first step in the development process, and will inform the work required before any decision on whether to progress the scheme is made, and if so, how to progress it.</p><p> </p><p>For both Western and Southern rail access, a summary of responses to the market testing will be published in due course.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Sugg",,"2018-11-28T16:47:02.993Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007485/answer","Biography information for Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007485/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007485/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-11-14","Heathrow Airport: Railways","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government when they expect to make a progress report on improvements in rail access to Heathrow Airport.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL11488"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007486","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-11-28","<p>The Government has no plans. Following the government’s decision to repeal Section 73 of the Copyright, Designs and Patents Act 1988, the Intellectual Property Office (IPO) conducted a technical consultation which looked at the broadcast rights market, the position of rights holders and whether new regulations would need to be introduced following the repeal. The consultation concluded that there was no need for new regulations as there are already extensive commercial rights agreements in place between relevant parties, which would be capable of factoring in new rights.</p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde",,"2018-11-28T15:18:42.567Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007486/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007486/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007486/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-11-14","Television: Royalties","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what plans they have, if any, for the future regulation of television content royalty payments.","false","Biography information for Lord Browne of Belmont",,"Lord Browne of Belmont","HL11489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007488","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-11-28","<p>An average cost per prisoner, costs per prison place and overall prison unit costs for each private and public sector prison in England and Wales are routinely published by Her Majesty’s Prison and Probation Service. This information is produced on an annual basis and is published after the end of each financial year.</p><p> </p><p>Information on prison expenditure can be accessed in the Prison and Probation Performance Statistics pages for each financial year on the <a href="http://www.gov.uk" target="_blank">www.gov.uk</a> website. Prison unit costs can be found within the Excel document titled Costs per prison place and cost per prisoner by individual prison establishment under the ‘Cost by Establishment’ tab.</p><p> </p><p>The most recent published figures for financial year 2017-18 can be accessed on the www.gov.uk website from the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/prison-performance-statistics-2017-to-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/prison-performance-statistics-2017-to-2018</a></p><p> </p><p>The table below shows the average annual overall cost per prisoner for financial years 2015-16 to 2017-18.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial years</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Average Annual Overall Cost per prisoner</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017-18</p></td><td><p>£37,543</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>£35,371</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>£33,931</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>To note within the table:</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><p>1. Figures are expressed in nominal terms as per published for respective years.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><p>2. Figures are not always comparable across a period due to changes in accounting treatments and scope of business which do not provide a consistent basis.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><p>3. Overall costs include the direct establishment costs plus expenditure met at regional or national level by HMPPS/MOJ.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>",,"Lord Keen of Elie",,"2018-11-28T13:56:25.13Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007488/answer","Biography information for Lord Keen of Elie","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007488/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007488/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-11-14","Prisoners: Per Capita Costs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what was the average annual cost of incarcerating a prisoner in (1) 2015, (2) 2016, and (3) 2017.","false","Biography information for Lord Browne of Belmont",,"Lord Browne of Belmont","HL11490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007489","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-22","<p>Intake for the Army Future Reserve 2020 between 1 January 2017 and 31 July 2018 was 6,513. Further information can be found on gov.uk at the link below:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/quarterly-service-personnel-statistics-2018</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2018-11-22T15:15:01.253Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007489/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007489/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007489/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-11-14","Army Reserve: Recruitment","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many volunteers were recruited to the Army Reserve between January 2017 and July 2018.","false","Biography information for Lord Browne of Belmont",,"Lord Browne of Belmont","HL11491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007490","Home Office","false","2018-11-28","<p>The Home Office is unable to disclose the requested information as it would substantially prejudice the operation of border controls by providing information to potential offenders allowing an opportunity for them to circumvent current systems and procedures used for the security of the UK border.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2018-11-28T17:32:58.963Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007490/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007490/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007490/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-14","Undocumented Migrants","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government in what locations non-UK citizens attempting to enter the UK illegally were apprehended in (1) 2015–16, and (2) 2016–17.","false","Biography information for Lord Browne of Belmont",,"Lord Browne of Belmont","HL11492"
