"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1006189","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-21","<p>We regularly raise issues concerning freedom of religion with the Government of Afghanistan, underlining, the need to protect the rights of all ethnic and religious groups in line with the constitution of Afghanistan.</p><p>We are concerned about the high number of civilian casualties and displaced persons that have resulted from the recent violence in Ghazni and Uruzgan. We urge that all parties to the conflict respect International Humanitarian Law, protecting the civilian population and facilitating the provision of assistance by neutral and impartial humanitarian agencies. We assess that the Afghan National Defence and Security Forces (ANDSF) are now working to stabilise the security situation in both provinces. We understand that those who have been displaced are receiving assistance from local authorities.</p><p>We continue to monitor the impact that fighting may have had on tensions between different communities. Ultimately, we urge all parties to negotiate a peaceful end to the conflict, which is causing the tragic death of innocent civilians.</p><p> </p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-11-21T12:08:54.007Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1006189/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1006189/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1006189/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-11-13","Afghanistan: Ethnic Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to the Afghanistan Government on protecting Hazaras people in Ghazni and Uruzgan provinces.","false","Biography information for Kate Osamor","Edmonton","Kate Osamor","190970"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1006190","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-11-19","<p>The Department has no targets for processing a mandatory reconsideration. Our focus is on ensuring the decision is correct. The time necessary to do this can depend on the circumstances of the case.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not administer appeals, which is the responsibility of HM Courts and Tribunals Service (HMCTS).</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","190865","2018-11-19T13:48:01.763Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1006190/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1006190/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1006190/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-11-13","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether her Department has a target timescale for processing the mandatory reconsiderations of its decisions on the eligibility of people for universal credit.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","190864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1006191","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-11-19","<p>The Department has no targets for processing a mandatory reconsideration. Our focus is on ensuring the decision is correct. The time necessary to do this can depend on the circumstances of the case.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not administer appeals, which is the responsibility of HM Courts and Tribunals Service (HMCTS).</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","190864","2018-11-19T13:48:01.807Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1006191/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1006191/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1006191/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-11-13","Universal Credit: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether her Department has a target timescale for hearing appeals against its decisions on the eligibility of people for universal credit.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","190865"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1006192","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-21","<p>NHS Property Services has 2,959 properties. The properties are broken down in the following regions:</p><p> </p><p>North West – 533 properties</p><p>East – 468 properties</p><p>South East – 459 properties</p><p>North Central – 357 properties</p><p>London – 347 properties</p><p>West Midlands – 289 properties</p><p>South West – 287 properties</p><p>North East – 219 properties</p><p>Total – 2,959 properties</p><p> </p><p>The number and split of assets managed by NHS Property Services is the same as the number of properties at 2,959. There are no further assets that NHS Property Services manage.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","190762 ; 190767","2018-11-21T14:50:24Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1006192/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1006192/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1006192/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-11-13","NHS Property Services: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what estimate he has made of the total number of assets managed by NHS Property Service.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","190761"
